<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c05e649-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1387"><num value="1387">§ 1387.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out the purposes of this subchapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6c05e64a-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1387/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> $2,400,000,000 for fiscal year 2022;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6c05e64b-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1387/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> $2,750,000,000 for fiscal year 2023;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6c05e64c-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1387/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> $3,000,000,000 for fiscal year 2024; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6c05e64d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1387/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> $3,250,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2025 and 2026.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id6c05e64e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-30/ch758">June 30, 1948, ch. 758</ref>, title VI, § 607, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/4/tII/s212/a">Pub. L. 100–4, title II, § 212(a)</ref>, <date date="1987-02-04">Feb. 4, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/26">101 Stat. 26</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/117/58/dE/tII/s50210/b">Pub. L. 117–58, div. E, title II, § 50210(b)</ref>, <date date="2021-11-15">Nov. 15, 2021</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/135/1169">135 Stat. 1169</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
